anar

Class SensitivityAnalysis

java.lang.Object
  anar.SensitivityAnalysis

public class SensitivityAnalysis
extends java.lang.Object

provide an engine to run sensitivity analysis on a provided computation function using the elementary effects method (Morris 1991, Campolongo 2007)

The elementary effects method is an instance of parameter screening method that enable to quantify the influence on some performance metric of a specified set of parameters.

analyze

public float[][] analyze(java.lang.Object o,
                         java.lang.String performanceName,
                         int nMaxTraj)
analyze previously computed sensitivity analysis results using a provided performance method (should be explicitely public)

Returns a bi-dimensional array of float with [i][0] = mu*, [i][1] = mu, [i][2] = sigma, [i][3] = number of trajectories used to compute the values

Assume the presence of trajectory information as well as pre-computed results. By defining nMaxTraj the user can restrict the number of trajectories considered in the analysis. Missing results are not taken into account.

The decoupling of computation and analysis allows for using different performance metrics on the same set of simulation results

Parameters:
o -
performanceName -
nMaxTraj -
